---
import Base from '../../hubs/web0/layouts/Base.astro';
import ToolLayout from '../../hubs/web0/components/ToolLayout.astro';
---
<Base
  title="RDAP Lookup - domain & IP registration data (WHOIS successor) | web0.dev"
  description="Look up domain and IP registration data via RDAP, the structured JSON successor to WHOIS. Runs in your browser against the official registries through the rdap.org bootstrap.">
  <ToolLayout name="RDAP Lookup" trust="queries the official RDAP registry for your input via the rdap.org bootstrap, directly from your browser.">
    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2">
        <input id="rdap-input" type="text" placeholder="google.com   ·   8.8.8.8" spellcheck="false"
          class="flex-1 bg-raised border border-rule rounded px-3 py-2 font-mono text-sm text-ink focus:outline-none focus:border-accent" />
        <button id="rdap-btn" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-medium bg-accent text-accent-ink px-4 py-2 rounded">Lookup</button>
      </div>
      <p id="rdap-status" class="label min-h-[1.2em]"></p>
      <div id="rdap-out"></div>
      <details id="rdap-raw-wrap" class="hidden border border-rule rounded">
        <summary class="label px-3 py-2 cursor-pointer">raw RDAP JSON</summary>
        <pre id="rdap-raw" class="p-3 text-xs font-mono text-ink overflow-auto max-h-96 whitespace-pre-wrap break-all"></pre>
      </details>
    </div>
    <div slot="explainer">
      <p>RDAP (Registration Data Access Protocol) is the structured, JSON-over-HTTPS successor to
      WHOIS. Classic WHOIS runs on TCP port 43, which a browser can't open. RDAP is plain HTTPS and
      ICANN's gTLD profile mandates <code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *</code>, so this works fully
      client-side.</p>
      <p class="mt-3">Works best for gTLDs (.com, .org, .dev, .io …) and IP allocations (ARIN/RIPE/APNIC).
      Some ccTLD registries don't expose CORS-enabled RDAP. Those fail honestly rather than guess.</p>
    </div>
  </ToolLayout>
</Base>
<script>
  import { rdapSection } from '../../hubs/web0/scripts/tools/rdap';
  rdapSection();
</script>
